                <h3>What are fractions?</h3>
<p>A <strong>fraction</strong> is part of a whole. It's <strong>less</stron=
g> than<strong> 1 </strong>whole thing, but more than <strong>0</strong>. W=
e use fractions all the time in real life. Have you ever ordered a <strong>=
quarter</strong>-pound burger? Or noticed that your gas tank is <strong>hal=
f</strong> full? Both of these are fractions of the whole amount=E2=80=94a =
whole pound of meat, or a whole tank of gas.</p>
<p>Fractions look a little like division expressions, but they aren't probl=
ems to be solved. They are a way of expressing an <strong>amount</strong>. =
Like numbers, fractions tell you <strong>how much</strong> you have of some=
thing.</p>
